choices.text: Blatnatalag, a friend of Iahub, managed to get hold of the problem before the contest. Because he wants to make sure Iahub will be the one qualified, he tells Iahub the following task. You're given an (1-based) array a with n elements. Let's define function f(i, j) (1   i, j   n) as (i - j)^2 + g(i, j)^2. Function g is calculated by the following pseudo-code: int g(int i, int j) {     int sum = 0;     for (int k = min(i, j) + 1; k <= max(i, j); k = k + 1)         sum = sum + a[k];     return sum; } Find a value min_{i}   j  f(i, j).
